entry.title: [BRP] Add BUILDFLAG that allows disabling optional OOB checks
entry.content:
OOB checks for operators ++/--/+=/-= aren't optional, as shifting a pointer to another slot without updating ref-counts would affect the integrity of the algorithm.



OOB checks for operator+/operator- are optional, because the resulting pointer will be written to a new raw_ptr<>, which will update ref-count properly. Even more so for operator[], which don't modify or create any pointers.



This CL is expected to be a no-op.

entry.title: [Blink] Refine GpuCanvasContext WebGPU SharedImage usage reference
entry.content:
GpuCanvasContext copies WebGPU textures to CanvasResourceProviders'

backing SharedImages via the WebGPU interface:



* Associating the backing SharedImage with a destination WebGPU texture

* Copying the source WebGPU texture into the destination WebGPU texture

* Disassociating the destination WebGPU texture with the backing

SharedImage (on the service side, this ends the Dawn access that was

initiated by the association)



It currently CHECKs that the backing SharedImage has

WEBGPU_READ | WEBGPU_WRITE usage, but for this purpose, the SI need

have only WEBGPU_WRITE usage.

entry.title: [fuchsia] Fix update_sdk.py to handle version:-prefix
entry.content:
DEPS mistakenly specifies the "fuchsia_version" with the CIPD

tag's "version:" prefix included in the version value. This breaks

the update_sdk.py scripts check of the version against the current

SDK version as per the "manifest.json", causing update_sdk.py to

always re-download the SDK.



Fix the update_sdk.py script to add the "version:" prefix to the

command-line version argument to create the CIPD tag.



Support for broken callers passing "version:" prefixed values is

temporarily retained.



The script is also updated to validate that the downloaded SDK

reports the expected version, so that similar mismatches will be

caught in future. The "Downloading Fuchsia SDK" message in DEPS is

corrected, and some log-spam is removed from the Fuchsia system-images

download script.

entry.title: Use new fields for key signature verification
entry.content:
The old signature for the public key,

new_public_key_verification_signature_deprecated has been deprecated

years ago. We need to start verifying the new key using the signature

provided by new_public_key_verification_data_signature. This will allow

the server side to stop computing the old signature for devices running

the new Chrome versions.



To reduce the risk, we keep the old signature verification as a backup.

The new histogram will allow us to check if the new signature works well

and is safe to remove the backup check.



The PolicyBuilder class used for tests had some signatures for that

can pass the verification used by the verification_key from

CloudPolicyValidator. Those signatures have been changed using a new

key and a mechanism to replace the verification_key for testing

purposed was implemented, since the new change required new signature

to be added. The existent tast tests and work with YAPS will continue

to pass because deprecated signature is used as a backup, but the plan

is to change that parts to use the same signatures and not include any

version in the new data to be signed.

entry.content:
Enabling/disabling MTE (Arm Memory Tagging Extension) requires a

reboot after running setprop. with_mte.py is a wrapper

script for tests that will enable MTE on the device for the

duration of the test.



bootctl property is set to MTE for the device.

We still need to enable MTE per app.

Chrome and tests enables MTE by default through the AndroidManifest.xml

https://source.android.com/docs/security/test/memory-safety/arm-mte#enable-mte-apps

And PartitionAlloc initialization will change the MTE mode to what is specified in Feature flags.

entry.title: [ProtegoPing] Add a new metric to log protego pings over 7 days
entry.content:
This change defines a new histogram called

SafeBrowsing.Enhanced.ProtegoRequestSentInLast7Days which is similar to

SafeBrowsing.Enhanced.ProtegoRequestSentIn24Hours. The difference is

that the new metric will record a type of WithToken or WithoutToken if a

ping was sent any time in the last 7 days.



We're landing this change so that we can get better visibility into how

many users are really logging None on each platform. Our hypothesis is

that if we look at the last ping across 7 days, then we'll see many less

None values logged. This will help us better understand the breakdown of

Protego ping composition in the Protego server logs.



This change also renames the method in the

safe_browsing_metrics_collector to `MaybeLogDailyEsbProtegoPingSent` to

better represent the contents -- since it no longer only logs values

related to 24 hours.
